(3512,	2,	'2019-05-02 16:44:26',	'2019-05-02 16:44:26',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>HOLLY, CO – April 30, 2019 </strong>– TBK Bank, SSB is proud to announce Kammie Cathcart, Vice President, Senior Relationship Manager, has been named 2019 Banker of the Year as a part of the Purposeful Banker Awards program.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The Purposeful Banker Awards honor a banker who shows dedication to their clients, to their community, and to their bank through exceptional, customized, and responsible customer service. The award recognizes a banker who builds meaningful relationships within their community through the work they do every day.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">“I am so honored to have been nominated and chosen to receive the Banker of the Year Award,” said Cathcart. “I am grateful to those on the TBK team who help me to help others each and every day. I appreciate those who nominated me and thank PrecisionLender for this prestigious award.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The award will be presented to Cathcart in a ceremony at the BankOnPurpose Conference in Austin on May 2, 2019. Many of the top baking institutions across the country, including TBK Bank, attend the BankOnPurpose Conference hosted by PrecisionLender. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In celebration of this great honor, TBK Bank invites members of the community to enjoy cake and punch at the Holly branch, located at 101 S Main Street, on Wednesday, May 8, 2019 between 10:00 a.m. and 4:00 p.m.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>About TBK Bank, SSB</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">TBK Bank, SSB, member FDIC and equal housing lender, is a subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK) offering consumer and commercial banking products from 61 branches throughout Iowa, Illinois, Colorado, Kansas, New Mexico, and Texas. https://tbkbank.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'TBK BANK\'S KAMMIE CATHCART NAMED BANKER OF THE YEAR',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'tbk-banks-kammie-cathcart-named-banker-of-the-year',	'',	'',	'2019-05-02 16:44:26',	'2019-05-02 16:44:26',	'',	0,	'https://tbkbank.com/?p=3512',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(3764,	4,	'2019-09-09 09:15:18',	'2019-09-09 09:15:18',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dallas – Sept. 9, 2019 – TBK Bank, SSB, a wholly owned subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK), is pleased to announced that Stephen D. Grossi has been appointed executive vice president, chief human resource officer of the bank. He will report to Aaron P. Graft, chief executive officer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this role, Grossi will direct the strategy of the bank’s human resources organization including talent management, training and development, benefits and compensation, change management, and human resource compliance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Steve is an energetic, results-oriented executive,” said Graft. “His record of making a positive impact at organizations at pivotal moments in their history makes him the ideal human resources leader for TBK. His leadership will be invaluable as we work to attract, develop and engage strong talent now and in the future.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Grossi joins TBK Bank from BOK Financial where he created and executed a transformative company-wide people and Human Resources strategy. Prior to that, he served as a Senior Vice President with PNC Financial Services where he led human resource efforts related to large acquisitions and realignments, workforce planning, organizational change, compensation and benefits, as well as talent acquisition and development. Mr. Grossi joined PNC with its acquisition of National City Bank in 2008. Prior to joining National City in December 2002, Mr. Grossi owned Capital Consultants, an HR consulting firm that specialized in the design of human capital strategies that link to and drive business results.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“TBK Bank is an impressive organization built on a strong culture that sets it apart from the competition,” said Grossi. “I look forward to working with the leadership and team members as we continue to set the standard for a best-in-class organization delivering exceptional value to our customers.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>ABOUT TBK BANK, SSB</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>TBK Bank, SSB, member FDIC and equal housing lender, is a subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK) offering consumer and commercial banking products from 61 branches throughout Iowa, Illinois, Colorado, Kansas, New Mexico, and Texas.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Media Contact: </strong>Amanda Tavackoli, SVP, Marketing &amp; Communication, TBK Bank, SSB |  atavackoli@tbkbank.com | 214-365-6930</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'TBK BANK APPOINTS STEPHEN D. GROSSI AS CHIEF HUMAN RESOURCE OFFICER',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'tbk-appoints-grossi-as-chro',	'',	'',	'2020-11-06 22:38:33',	'2020-11-06 22:38:33',	'',	0,	'https://tbkbank.com/?p=3764',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(4246,	5,	'2019-12-02 15:21:01',	'2019-12-02 15:21:01',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dallas – Dec. 2, 2019 – TBK Bank, SSB, a wholly owned subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK), is pleased to announced that Alan Nykiel has been appointed chief marketing officer of the bank. He will report to Aaron P. Graft, chief executive officer. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this role, Nykiel will be responsible for developing and executing the marketing strategies in support of the strategic plans for multiple brands including TBK Bank, Triumph Commercial Finance, Triumph Insurance, Triumph Business Capital and TriumphPay. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Alan is a natural fit to lead marketing and communication for TBK Bank,” said Graft. “He has an impressive track record of managing marketing programs for fast growing, dynamic financial institutions. His experience in strategic planning, integrated, data-driven marketing, and customer experience will provide critical leadership as we pursue new strategies and introduce innovative solutions to the market.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Alan Joins TBK Bank from BOK Financial where he most recently served as Chief Marketing and Communication Officer. In this role, he was responsible for client and employee-focused brand, marketing and communication. He led strategic initiatives and accelerated change in the areas of brand management, marketing, communication, digital, social, analytics and insights, client experience, research and corporate social responsibility. Prior to BOK Financial, Alan served in a variety of senior marketing leadership roles with Amegy Bank in Houston, TX, Regions Bancorporation in Birmingham, AL, and Bank United in Houston, TX. He has served on various boards, including Parkside Children’s Psychiatric Hospital and M.D. Anderson Cancer Research.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“TBK Bank is a values-driven organization with a people-first culture,” said Nykiel. “It has established itself as a high-quality, high-growth organization focused on the clients and communities it serves. I look forward to working in partnership with the leadership team and team members to nurture and accelerate the growth of their diversified business model.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>About TBK Bank, SSB</strong><br>\nTBK Bank, SSB, member FDIC and equal housing lender, is a subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK) offering consumer and commercial banking products from 61 branches throughout Iowa, Illinois, Colorado, Kansas, New Mexico, and Texas. https://tbkbank.com </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Media Contact:</strong><br>\nAmanda Tavackoli<br>\nSVP, Communication<br>\nTBK Bank, SSB<br>\natavackoli@tbkbank.com | 214-365-693</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'TBK BANK APPOINTS ALAN NYKIEL AS CHIEF MARKETING OFFICER',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'tbk-bank-appoints-alan-nykiel-as-chief-marketing-officer',	'',	'',	'2020-11-06 22:38:33',	'2020-11-06 22:38:33',	'',	0,	'https://tbkbank.com/?p=4246',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(4265,	4,	'2019-12-12 22:49:21',	'2019-12-12 22:49:21',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>GRANADA, CO. – December 12, 2019 – TBK Bank, SSB, donated its building, located at 205 E Goff Avenue, to the Granada School District No. RE-1 in a key handing ceremony this morning. The building will subsequently be converted to the new location for the Amache Museum, which is dedicated to conserving the Amache site and its World War II history as the Granada War Relocation Center.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The donation of the bank’s 4,800 square foot building will allow the Amache Preservation Society (APS) to relocate and expand the current Amache Museum located across US-50 from the new site. The building will provide additional space for educational exhibitions and presentations as well as a dedicated research space to be used by Denver University and Colorado College research teams while studying the former World War II internment camp.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“TBK Bank is committed to serving the people, business and community of Granada,” said Lesli Baca, Vice President, Regional Operations Manager for TBK Bank. “The Granada School District and the Amache Preservation Society play an important role in preserving the history of our community and we are honored to be a part of that with this donation.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The Granada School District is honored and humbled to receive this building from TBK Bank,” said Ty Kemp, Superintendent of the Granada School District No. RE-1. “This building will be used to expand our Amache Museum and to provide research space for our high school students and for people from all over America that visit the museum. We truly appreciate the community minded spirit in which this building was donated and TBK supporting the educational efforts and growth of our students and school. This donation will touch the lives of students and visitors for many years to come.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The Japanese American Communities across the United States will be thrilled with this new museum,” said John Hopper, founder of the Amache Preservation Society and Dean of Students for the Granada School District.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The building, which previously served as an operations center for TBK Bank, is also the site of the bank’s drive through ATM. The ATM will remain in place and continue to operate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>###</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>ABOUT TBK BANK, SSB</strong><br>\nTBK Bank, SSB, member FDIC and equal housing lender, is a subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK) offering consumer and commercial banking products from 61 branches throughout Iowa, Illinois, Colorado, Kansas, New Mexico, and Texas.<a href=\"https://tbkbank.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"> https://tbkbank.com</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>ABOUT THE GRANADA SCHOOL DISTRICT NO. RE-1</strong><br>\nThe Granada School District No. RE-1 is a public school district located in Granada, Colorado, educating students from PK through 12th grade. <a href=\"https://www.granadaschools.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.granadaschools.org/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>ABOUT THE AMACHE PRESERVATION SOCIETY</strong><br>\nThe Amache Preservation Society (APS) is responsible for maintaining the physical site of Amache, a World War II internment camp located in Granada, Colorado. The society, established by Mr. John Hopper, is run by student volunteers and has been instrumental in the renovation of the cemetery and the establishment of the Amache Museum and research center. APS has restored key Amache landmarks including the water tower, guard tower and barrack. <a href=\"https://amache.org/amache-preservation-society/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://amache.org/amache-preservation-society/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'TBK BANK DONATES BUILDING TO GRANADA SCHOOL DISTRICT',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'tbk-bank-donates-building-to-granada-school-district',	'',	'',	'2020-11-06 22:38:33',	'2020-11-06 22:38:33',	'',	0,	'https://tbkbank.com/?p=4265',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(4391,	4,	'2020-02-11 17:19:17',	'2020-02-11 17:19:17',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BAYFIELD, CO – February 11, 2020 –TBK Bank, SSB today announced the donation of $5,000 to the Bayfield Education Foundation. As a major educational driver for the community of Bayfield, the Bayfield Education Foundation has recently begun supporting the Pueblo Community College (PCC) satellite campus located in Bayfield. The TBK Bank donation will be used to create scholarships for PCC students and to support the Community Treehouse, an indoor play area that provides supervised play for children ages 0-10 while their parents are in the Treehouse lounge or at PCC classes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":4385} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignright\"><img src=\"https://tbkbank.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/TBK-BAYFIELD-DONATION-01-2020.jpg\" alt=\"TBK Bank Makes Donation to Bayfield Education Foundation\" class=\"wp-image-4385\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Bayfield Education Foundation’s purpose is to provide the means by which educational opportunities are made available to the community through scholarships, class sponsorships, and supporting organizations that help dismantle barriers to education,” said Melissa Zimmerman, Market Sales Manager for TBK Bank. “TBK Bank is very proud to sponsor this organization as we know the needed funds will be distributed to provide the greatest impact in Bayfield and surrounding communities.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Barbara Wickman, secretary of the Bayfield Education Foundation, explained that a portion of this donation will be used to support PCC students “for instructional support at K-12, capital projects at Bayfield schools, pre-school scholarships, and college scholarships for this year’s BHS seniors.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Our commitment to the community of Bayfield goes deeper than monetary donations,” said Zimmerman. “TBK Bank will also provide three free financial literacy courses at the PCC campus in 2020. Each class will be held at 4:00pm and 5:30pm on various days. On March 24th, the class will focus on money basics, such as spending habits; the June 2nd class will focus on protecting your money and knowing how to spot scams; the October 6th class will focus on holiday gift budgeting.” Free, supervised play at the Community Treehouse will be provided for the children of those attending these classes. If you’re interested in attending please contact Melissa Zimmerman at (970) 426-4331 or mzimmerman@tbkbank.com.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>###</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>About TBK Bank, SSB</strong><br>\nTBK Bank, SSB, member FDIC and equal housing lender, is a subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK) offering consumer and commercial banking products from 61 branches throughout Iowa, Illinois, Colorado, Kansas, New Mexico, and Texas. <a href=\"https://tbkbank.com\">https://tbkbank.com</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>About Bayfield Education Foundation</strong><br>\nThe Bayfield Education Foundation was established in 2015. Since then, the group has supported, enhanced and advanced the learning environment of the Bayfield School District by filling under-recognized and under-funded educational needs to help children and adults build a bright future. <a href=\"http://bayfieldeducationfoundation.org/\">http://bayfieldeducationfoundation.org/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'TBK BANK DONATES $5,000 TO BAYFIELD EDUCATION FOUNDATION',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'tbk-bank-donates-to-bayfield-education-foundation',	'',	'',	'2020-11-06 22:38:32',	'2020-11-06 22:38:32',	'',	0,	'https://tbkbank.com/?p=4391',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(4413,	5,	'2020-02-26 21:29:53',	'2020-02-26 21:29:53',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ten Hardworking Students Will be Awarded $1,000 Scholarships</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>February 26, 2020 – DALLAS – TBK Bank, SSB announced today that it is now accepting applications for its 2020 TBK Scholars Program, which will award ten $1,000 scholarships to hard working students seeking to make a difference in their communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Applicants are asked to write an essay about how they will use their education to make a difference right here in our community,” said John DeDoncker, President of the Midwest Division of TBK Bank. “It’s exciting to learn about the big dreams these students have for their futures and the passion they have to use their education to make their community better.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This scholarship program is based on the following criteria:<br>\n   •A high school senior on track to graduate in the Spring of 2020<br>\n   •A current resident in a county where TBK Bank currently has a branch<br>\n   •Entering an accredited 2 or 4 year school in the Fall of 2020 as a freshman<br>\n   •Must be able to provide documentation on high school transcripts and college acceptance<br>\n   •Must demonstrate financial need, as determined by family income level<br>\n   •Write 750-word Personal Essay Statement </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the full list of eligibility details and to access the application, please visit the TBK Bank’s website <a href=\"/tbkscholars/\">https://tbkbank.com/tbkscholars/</a>. If you have any questions about the scholarship or about accepted forms of income verification, please email scholarship@tbkbank.com. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All completed applications must be delivered to a local TBK Bank branch no later than Wednesday, April 15, 2020.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“We are excited to continue the TBK Scholars Program in 2020,” said Brandi Dunn, Director of Community Engagement for TBK Bank. “Training Future Leaders is one of our core philanthropic values and this scholarship program allows us to invest in our local communities by investing in local students.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is the second year for the TBK Scholars program. Last year’s recipients attended College of the Holy Cross, Fort Hays State University, Illinois State, Judson University, Otero Junior College, St. Ambrose University, The University of Texas at Arlington, University of Colorado Bounder, University of Northern Colorado and University of Utah.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2019 TBK Scholars Program recipient Emily Brodbeck recently told the company, “I just completed my first semester at St. Ambrose University in Davenport, Iowa. Academically, I was particularly challenged in my biology course in which I conducted my own scientific research at a nearby marsh. I want to thank TBK Bank once again for your contribution to my higher education as I work towards becoming a Doctor of Physical Therapy.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>TBK Bank created the TBK Scholars Program in 2019 with the goal of helping train future leaders in the communities it serves. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'TBK BANK NOW ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS FOR TBK SCHOLARS PROGRAM',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'tbk-bank-now-accepting-applications-for-tbk-scholars-program',	'',	'',	'2020-11-06 22:38:32',	'2020-11-06 22:38:32',	'',	0,	'https://tbkbank.com/?p=4413',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(4607,	4,	'2020-04-08 14:00:52',	'2020-04-08 14:00:52',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BETTENDORF, IOWA (April 8, 2020) -- TBK Bank, SSB, a wholly owned subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK), today announced it will relocate its Midwest division headquarters to downtown Bettendorf in 2021.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>TBK Bank has 18 branches in its Midwest division, 10 of which are located in the Quad Cities. “TBK Bank is committed to Bettendorf and the Quad Cities,” said John DeDoncker, Midwest Division President of TBK Bank. “Relocating our headquarters to downtown Bettendorf reinforces this commitment to this community. We are excited to move into a location that affords us more space and increased amenities for our team members and customers.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MBGA, LLC, a Bettendorf-based real estate developer, began construction on the building TBK Bank will occupy in January 2020. “We felt this location, just east of the new I-74 bridge and north of the Bridges apartments, would attract interest to downtown Bettendorf,” said Kevin Koellner, one of the principals of MBGA. “TBK Bank has been an excellent member of our community for so many years and we are thrilled that they will serve as the anchor tenant in our new building.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bank’s current Midwest Division headquarters is located at Duck Creek Plaza on Middle Road, where it has been for almost 20 years. All team members from that location are expected to relocate into the new space in summer 2021.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“While we’re only relocating 2 miles from our current location, it is a significant moment for our team members who have all played a critical role in bringing us where we are today,” said DeDoncker. “We are proud of this milestone and look forward to creating a division headquarters that is not only designed to support our unique culture and team member experience, but also to create a new and better branch experience for our customers and the Quad Cities community.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 2019, TBK Bank also <a href=\"https://tbkbank.com/tbk-bank-to-donate-downtown-banking-facility-to-east-moline-public-library/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">announced</a> the donation of its East Moline branch to the East Moline Library. The bank constructed a new branch in East Moline that is expected to open later this spring.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The downtown building will include four stories with the bank’s branch, a restaurant and other retail shops on the first floor. The bank will also occupy the second and third floors with operational and back office staff. Build to Suit, Inc. operates as the general contractor for the project with Streamline Architects, Carr Engineering and IMEG providing architectural and engineering services.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">###</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>About TBK Bank, SSB</strong><br>\nTBK Bank, SSB, member FDIC and equal housing lender, is a subsidiary of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. (Nasdaq: TBK) offering consumer and commercial banking products from 61 branches throughout Iowa, Illinois, Colorado, Kansas, New Mexico, and Texas. <a href=\"https://tbkbank.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://tbkbank.com</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Media Contact</strong><br>\nAmanda Tavackoli<br>\nSVP, Marketing &amp; Communication<br>\natavackoli@tbkbank.com  |  214.365.6930</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'TBK BANK TO RELOCATE ITS MIDWEST DIVISION HEADQUARTERS IN BETTENDORF',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'tbk-bank-to-relocate-its-midwest-division-headquarters-in-bettendorf',	'',	'\nhttps://tbkbank.com/tbk-bank-to-donate-downtown-banking-facility-to-east-moline-public-library/',	'2020-11-06 22:38:30',	'2020-11-06 22:38:30',	'',	0,	'https://tbkbank.com/?p=4607',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(4897,	5,	'2020-06-01 19:36:06',	'2020-06-01 19:36:06',	'<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>BRANCH CLOSING ALERT</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Due to the Quad Cities shelter in place order, TBK Bank will be closing all of our branches in the Quad Cities at 3:00 PM today 6/1 and will not reopen until 10:00 am tomorrow, 6/2.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The safety of our team members, customers and communities remains our top priority during this time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We encourage you to bank with us online or with the TBK Bank Mobile App.  You can also reach Customer Care at 866-644-3935. We continue to pray for everyone’s health and safety during this difficult time. Please continue to visit this page and social media for up-to –date information. Please stay safe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Branch List:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>IOWA:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bettendorf</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Davenport- Jersey Ridge (CLOSED 6/1)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Davenport- West Kimberly (CLOSED 6/1)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>ILLINOIS:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>East Moline - 8th Street</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>East Moline - Avenue of the Cities</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Milan</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moline - 1st Street</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moline - 48th Street</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rapids City</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Silvis</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Branch Closing Alert - June 1, 2020',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'branch-alert-june1-