(5758,	1,	'2020-11-23 21:43:43',	'2020-11-23 21:43:43',	'<!-- wp:acf/wrapper {\n    \"id\": \"block_5fbc2ce5e0681\",\n    \"name\": \"acf\\/wrapper\",\n    \"data\": {\n        \"generous_vertical_padding\": \"0\",\n        \"_generous_vertical_padding\": \"field_5f6e04852a13b\",\n        \"show_layout_options\": \"1\",\n        \"_show_layout_options\": \"field_5f579b546ee17\",\n        \"width\": \"container-md\",\n        \"_width\": \"field_5f5798a171a9f\",\n        \"background_color\": \"transparent\",\n        \"_background_color\": \"field_5f57993c71aa0\"\n    },\n    \"align\": \"\",\n    \"mode\": \"preview\"\n} -->\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>Security Policy</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This Internet Banking System brings together a combination of industry-approved security technologies to protect data for the bank and for you, our customer. It features password- controlled system entry, a VeriSign-issued Digital ID for the bank\'s server, Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) protocol for data encryption, and a firewall to regulate the inflow and outflow of server traffic.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Secure Access and Verifying User Authenticity</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you login to our Internet banking site, the page that the login form is posting to is secured using SSL, https://ss1.tbkbank.com. There are two ways to verify this. The first is to watch the address bar after you submit the login. It should change to a site with \\\'https://ss1.bankwithtriumph.com\' for just a second before sending you to our Internet banking site. The second and more technical way to verify that we are providing you with a secure login is to view the source on the login page. If you search for the \'FORM\' element, the \'action\' attribute will be a URL that starts with https://ss1.tbkbank.com. HTTPS is HyperText Transport Protocol (Secure), the standard encrypted communication mechanism on the World Wide Web. This is also known as HTTP over SSL.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Secure Data Transfer</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the server session is established, the user and the server are in a secured, encrypted environment. Because the server has been certified as a 128-bit secure server by VeriSign, data traveling between the user and the server is encrypted with Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) protocol. With SSL, data that travels between the bank and customer is encrypted and can only be decrypted with the public and private key pair. In short, the bank\'s server issues a public key to the end user\'s browser and creates a temporary private key. These two keys are the only combination possible for that session. When the session is complete, the keys expire and the whole process starts over when a new user makes a server session.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Firewall</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Data requests must filter through a firewall before they are permitted to reach the server. The firewall configuration begins by disallowing ALL traffic and then allows traffic only when necessary to process acceptable data requests, such as retrieving web pages or sending customer requests to the bank. Using the above technologies, your Internet banking transactions are secure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- /wp:acf/wrapper -->',	'Security Policy',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'security-policy',	'',	'',	'2020-11-23 21:48:27',	'2020-11-23 21:48:27',	'',	5623,	'http://tbknew.local/?page_id=5758',	0,	'page',	'',	0),
(5759,	1,	'2020-11-23 21:47:44',	'2020-11-23 21:47:44',	'<!-- wp:acf/wrapper {\n    \"id\": \"block_5fbc2d84c5b26\",\n    \"name\": \"acf\\/wrapper\",\n    \"data\": {\n        \"generous_vertical_padding\": \"0\",\n        \"_generous_vertical_padding\": \"field_5f6e04852a13b\",\n        \"show_layout_options\": \"1\",\n        \"_show_layout_options\": \"field_5f579b546ee17\",\n        \"width\": \"container-md\",\n        \"_width\": \"field_5f5798a171a9f\",\n        \"background_color\": \"transparent\",\n        \"_background_color\": \"field_5f57993c71aa0\"\n    },\n    \"align\": \"\",\n    \"mode\": \"preview\"\n} -->\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>Social Media Policy</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Triumph Bancorp, Inc. and its subsidiaries (“Triumph”) are excited to be a part of social media so we can communicate with you in your online communities. In order to keep our conversations on track and your personal information safe online, we’ve created a list of some helpful guidelines to remember.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Your Private Information</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Triumph won’t be able to respond to your specific bank account questions through social media. To discuss concerns about your bank account, please contact one of branch banking locations. We will never ask you to provide this type of information through Facebook, Twitter, blogs or any other type of public channel.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Comments by Employees</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Triumph does not endorse any comments made by its employees, unless they are an authorized representative of the bank. All unofficial statements and viewpoints expressed in the comments are strictly those of the commenter alone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Endorsements</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Triumph is not responsible for and does not endorse any content or advertisements posted by social media sites or of third party sites or applications that may appear on those social media sites.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Affiliation</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Triumph has a brand presence on social media sites; please note that Triumph is not affiliated with these sites. Triumph has no control over how third parties use the information you share on these sites. Your participation in social media is at your own risk. We also recommend that you would familiarize yourself with the social media privacy policies of all social media sites before using them. We will not affiliate with sites where the age requirement is below 13 to follow the guidelines of COPPA.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Responsibility of Security</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Triumph is not responsible for the privacy or security on social media sites and other third-party sites that may be linked to social media sites.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Validity of Links</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Users should be aware when they click on a link on a Triumph social media page, they assume the risk. Users should also understand that they may be leaving our site when clicking on such links. Users should exercise extra caution when links are posted outside of normal business hours or on third party comments. We may occasionally post links to third-party sites when we think you’ll find the information helpful. However, please note that this does not in any way constitute an official endorsement of the individual, information, site or company.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Removal of Comments</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All Triumph social media sites are monitored, and any posts considered obscene, pornographic or similarly inappropriate will be removed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have a question or a comment for us, post away! Please note that these pages are moderated by Triumph employees. We will make every effort to respond in a timely manner Monday through Friday between 8 a.m. and 5 p.m. Central time, (excluding Holidays).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Community &amp; Thought Leadership Disclaimer&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The views and opinions expressed in the Community &amp; Thought Leadership blog are those of the individual contributor and do not necessarily reflect those of Triumph Bancorp, Inc. or any of its related companies. Comments posted in response to blog posts are the opinions of the readers. In no event will Triumph Bancorp, Inc. or any of its related companies be liable for any loss or damage including without limitation, indirect or consequential loss or damage, or any loss or damage whatsoever arising from loss of data or profits arising out of, or in connection with, the use of this blog. Statements contained in this blog, which are not historical facts, including statements about plans, goals and expectations regarding businesses and opportunities, new or existing business strategies, capital resources and future financial results are “forward looking” as contemplated by the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. Such forward-looking statements are subject to risks and uncertainties, including, but not limited to, changes in government regulation, generally accepted accounting principles, taxation, competition, general economic conditions and geopolitical conditions. Accordingly, actual results may differ materially from those projected or implied in the forward-looking statements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n<!-- /wp:acf/wrapper -->',	'Social Media Policy',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'social-media-policy',	'',	'',	'2020-11-23 21:57:17',	'2020-11-23 21:57:17',	'',	5623,	'http://tbknew.local/?page_id=5759',	0,	'page',	'',	0),
